id: pm-a2h3
title: "Notes/learnings repair parity: add --edit/--delete (and a real --stdin/--file input source) matching comments, so bad annotation entries are fixable via the CLI"
description: "Comments support --edit <index>/--delete <index> plus [text]/--add/--stdin/--file input sources; notes and learnings are append-only with only --add (stdin via '--add -'). review #11 hit this live: a bogus note ('--stdin', see pm-vcu7) on milestone pm-doxj could not be corrected by any pm command and required manual .toon + history revert — violating the philosophy that agents rebuild and maintain full context via the pm CLI alone. Duplicate check 2026-07-06: pm-yql1 consolidates facet GRAMMAR (zero feature loss, no new verbs); pm-9y8q (closed) deduped internals; no open item adds edit/delete to notes/learnings."
type: Task
